Cape Town - An electrical short-circuit caused a fire in Salt River, Cape Town on Thursday morning. "The City's Fire and Rescue Service responded to Dollars Fast-food Take-away at 06:18 this morning," the department's Theo Layne said. "The fire was confined to the kitchen area of the take-away with the remainder of the building sustaining smoke and some water damage. Two fire engines, one rescue vehicle and one hydraulic platform responded from Salt River and Roeland Street Fire Stations (16 Firefighters.) "The Fire was extinguished and the building ventilated by 07:30. No injuries were reported," Layne said. The cause of the fire was an electrical short-circuit, he said. Cape Argus